## Documentation Closure

**Disposal Report:**

The formal record of the disposal process, prepared by the ISSO and reviewed by the Health IT Manager and Compliance Officer:

| Section | Content |
|---|---|
| System identification | MCOPENMRS-001; decommission date |
| Reason for disposal | [System replacement / upgrade / retirement] |
| Archive inventory | Patient records archive location, encryption key ARN, retention period; authorization package archive location |
| Destruction confirmation | List of all destroyed resources with confirmation timestamps |
| KMS key disposal | Keys deleted: [list with deletion dates]; Key retained: [archive key ARN, retention period] |
| Access revocation record | All user accounts, IAM entities, and third-party connections revoked as of [date] |
| Verification attestation | ISSO signature — archive verification checklist completed before destruction began |
| Compliance Officer review | Confirmation that HIPAA retention obligations have been met |

**SSP closure annotation:**
The SSP is annotated with a decommission header: "SYSTEM DECOMMISSIONED [date]. This document is retained for historical reference per HIPAA documentation requirements. The system described herein is no longer operational. See Disposal Report [date] for decommissioning record."

**System registry update:**
The system registry entry is updated: Authorization Status — DECOMMISSIONED [date]. Archival location noted for future reference.

